# Azure Deployment Plan for statcompy Project
## Goal
Deploy the existing `backend` and `frontend` services to the already provisioned Azure Container Apps in resource group `statcompy-rg` and subscription `bb5b48c3-99b9-45e5-bc12-81e929c4a823` using Azure CLI.

## Project Information
**statcompy**
- **Stack**: NestJS backend and Angular frontend, both TypeScript
- **Type**: Business operations platform with payroll, compliance, CRM, audit, and contractor modules
- **Containerization**: Dockerfiles already exist at `backend/Dockerfile` and `frontend/Dockerfile`
- **Dependencies**: Azure Database for PostgreSQL, Azure Storage, Azure Container Registry
- **Hosting**: Azure Container Apps for both backend and frontend

## Azure Resources Architecture
> Install the mermaid extension in IDE to view the architecture.
```mermaid
graph TD
svc_backend["`Name: backend
Path: backend
Language: ts`"]
svc_frontend["`Name: frontend
Path: frontend
Language: ts`"]

subgraph compute["Compute Resources"]
subgraph env["Azure Container Apps Environment"]
aca_backend("`statcompy-backend
Azure Container App`")
aca_frontend("`statcompy-frontend
Azure Container App`")
end
end

subgraph deps["Dependency Resources"]
pg["`statcompy-db
Azure Database for PostgreSQL`"]
acr["`statcompyacr001
Azure Container Registry`"]
storage["`uploadstorage
Azure Files / Storage`"]
end

svc_backend -->|hosted on| aca_backend
svc_frontend -->|hosted on| aca_frontend
aca_backend -.->|secret| pg
aca_backend -.->|system-identity| acr
aca_backend -.->|secret| storage
aca_frontend -.->|http| aca_backend
aca_frontend -.->|system-identity| acr
```

## Existing Azure Resources
| Resource Type | Name | SKU | Purpose |
|---------------|------|-----|---------|
| Container App | statcompy-backend | Consumption | Backend API service |
| Container App | statcompy-frontend | Consumption | Frontend web service |
| Container Apps Environment | statcompy-env | Consumption | Shared ACA environment |
| Azure Container Registry | statcompyacr001 | Basic | Stores backend/frontend images |
| Azure Database for PostgreSQL | statcompy-db | Flexible Server | Production application database |
| Azure Storage / Azure Files | uploadstorage | Standard_LRS | Backend uploads volume |

## Missing Resource
No missing resource is assumed initially. Validate existence before deployment.

## Execution Step
- [x] Containerization: confirmed Dockerfiles at `backend/Dockerfile` and `frontend/Dockerfile`
- [ ] Env setup for Azure CLI
- [ ] Validate existing Azure resources
- [ ] Build and push backend image to ACR
- [ ] Build and push frontend image to ACR
- [ ] Update backend Container App image
- [ ] Update frontend Container App image
- [ ] Validate deployment via logs and health endpoints
- [ ] Summarize deployment result

## Progress Tracking
- Update `.azure/progress.copilotmd` after each completed deployment step.

